name: ethyl 4-cyanophenylacetate
Reason: 4-Cyanophenyl can increase the melting point due to the additional pi-system and rigidity, estimated at around +20°C. The cyano group introduces a strong withdrawing group, raising the melting point by approximately +50°C. The methyl group reduces the melting point due to the reduced molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, estimated at around -10°C. The carbonyl group raises the melting point due to the potential for hydrogen bonding and dipole-dipole interactions, estimated at around +10°C.
